div.div: Opened #198 CSS background property showing under invalid.deprecated scope despite not being invalid/deprecated.
Why is the transition: background red in syntax highlighting (Visual Studio)?

Answer The syntax is red because VSCode marked it as invalid/deprecated code, and the Dark+ theme has this scope set to #F44747 (red). Override default style In case you're looking to change the default foreground (color) or the default fontStyle of this scope, you can go to vscode command prompt and select Open settings (JSON) then add the following : "editor.tokenColorCustomizations": { "[Default Dark+]": { (11 more lines were trimmed) Result:
Match background with users current weather conditions
